def remove_outliers_iqr(df):
    # Create a copy of the DataFrame to avoid modifying the original data
    df_cleaned = data.copy()

    # Iterate over each feature (column)
    for feature in data.columns:
        # Calculate Q1 (25th percentile) and Q3 (75th percentile)
        Q1 = data[feature].quantile(0.25)
        Q3 = data[feature].quantile(0.75)
        
        # Calculate the IQR (Interquartile Range)
        IQR = Q3 - Q1
        
        # Define the lower and upper bounds for outliers
        lower_bound = Q1 - 1.75 * IQR
        upper_bound = Q3 + 1.75 * IQR
        
        # Filter out the outliers
        df_cleaned = df_cleaned[(df_cleaned[feature] >= lower_bound) & (df_cleaned[feature] <= upper_bound)]
    
    return df_cleaned

# Example usage:
# Assuming 'data' is your DataFrame
df = remove_outliers_iqr(data)

# To check the shape of the cleaned data
print(f"Original data shape: {data.shape}")
print(f"Cleaned data shape: {df.shape}")

Feature Importance¶

In [23]:
# Drop irrelevant features
dgt = df.drop(columns=[ 'Ym', 'R', 'CaO', 'D3A', 'D3B','DS2A', 'DS2B', 'POA', 'POB', 'TsA', 'TsB', 'SFA', 'SFB', 'DgA', 'DgB', 'CaoA', 'CaoB'])

# Define target variables and feature variables
target_vars = ['YseA', 'YseB', 'YsynA', 'YsynB', 'YuntA', 'YuntB']

features = dgt.columns.difference(target_vars)

# Initialize the model
rf = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)

# Function to plot feature importances for each target variable in ascending order
def plot_feature_importances(target, feature_importances, features):
    # Create a DataFrame with feature importances
    feature_importance_df = pd.DataFrame({'Feature': features, 'Importance': feature_importances})
    # Sort by importance in ascending order
    feature_importance_df = feature_importance_df.sort_values(by='Importance', ascending=True)
    
    # Plot the feature importances
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.barh(feature_importance_df['Feature'], feature_importance_df['Importance'])
    plt.xlabel('Feature Importance')
    plt.ylabel('Features')
    plt.title(f'Feature Importance for {target}')
    plt.show()

# Calculate and plot feature importances for each target variable
for target in target_vars:
    rf.fit(dgt[features], dgt[target])
    importances = rf.feature_importances_
    plot_feature_importances(target, importances, features)

Mutual importance analysis¶

In [52]:
# Separate features and target
X = dgt.drop(target_vars, axis=1)

# Calculate mutual information for each target variable
mi_scores = {}

for target in target_vars:
    y = dgt[target]
    # Set a fixed random_state for reproducibility
    mi = mutual_info_regression(X, y, random_state=42)
    mi_scores[target] = pd.Series(mi, index=X.columns).sort_values(ascending=False)

    # Plot histogram
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))
    mi_scores[target].plot(kind='bar', color='skyblue', edgecolor='black')
    
    plt.title(f"Mutual Information Scores for Target: {target}")
    plt.xlabel("Features")
    plt.ylabel("Mutual Information")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
